  &lt;p id="tN10jy"&gt;Threads is working on a new community feature that will seemingly allow users to group together around particular topics and interests, &lt;a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/10/08/metas-threads-app-references-a-communities-feature-similar-to-elon-musks-x/?utm_source=dlvr.it&amp;amp;utm_medium=threads"&gt;&lt;em&gt;TechCrunch&lt;/em&gt; reports&lt;/a&gt;. Developer &lt;a href="https://www.threads.net/@chris/post/DA1nBkKzZhP"&gt;Chris Messina spotted references to “Loops”&lt;/a&gt; in the code for Threads’ latest app update, which vaguely describes something similar to the “Communities” feature on X or even subreddits.&lt;/p&gt;
